history.text: Hello! What did you think of the movie Batman vs Superman?
This movie was terrible. The ratings show others agree with me. Did you like it?
Not really. I like Batman movies, but this movie was not good. I don't like Ben Affleck as Batman, either.
The only thing I liked about this movie was that Wonder Woman made an appearance.

Yeah. I like some of the other actors in the movie. I tend to like Amy Adams and Diane Lane. I typically don't like Jesse Eisenberg or Ben Affleck. And yes! This was the first live-action cinematic portrayal of Wonder Woman.
It was only 153 minutes, but still seemed too long!
I think the review that it "wasn't fun" was accurate, because I agree, it took way too long.
Man of Steel wasn't a good movie either, and I don't think this movie was better.
Definitely. But I did like the review that said it was just "whacking two dolls together"
They were both equally bad in my mind.
It definitely wasn't as good as Dark Knight
Whacking dolls together DOES seem appropriate for the fight scenes...
It's hard to even keep track of the plot. I don't remember it well.  I don't remember Luther importing anything.
Now I see a 'key scenes' box. I guess he imported kryptonite.
I love that it only has a 27% Rotten Tomatoes score. That's pretty bad
I think it's hard to understand some points in the movie without remembering some of Man of Steel, since Zod's death plays an important role in this movie.
I use Rotten Tomatoes often for movie reviews; they tend to be very accurate for recent movies.
Well clearly with the scene description this movie starts 18 months after the Superman/Zod battle. That's a helpful little description box
Why is Luthor explaining that he fueled the feud? Is he just bragging/rubbing their faces in it?
I'm glad they explained the Martha thing, I would not have remembered that.

I think Luther just wanted to give Superman a reason to kill Batman AND feel bad about it. Basically telling Superman "Hey, I made you guys hate each other but you never needed to, and now you have to kill him."
I'm not sure how Batman could be confused about Martha, as his mother is long dead.
I'm glad Wonder Woman appears in this film, so that the women aren't just standing around waiting to get kidnapped. Ok. Luthor gets an extra power kick that way. Makes sense.
"...Wait, can this dude time travel now?" haha
That would be an interesting super power for Superman, but would ruin the story.
Wait... how is Wonder Woman in this movie but is not included in the key scenes?
Meh, she's got her own movie. I don't know.
Her role is important enough for the introduction but she isn't even mentioned in the cast or the key scenes.
You're right, it does seem strange.
This movie was clearly setting up for another movie when Batman discussed making a team of Metahumans.
Yes, I was about to comment on that. Bruce feels like a failure and makes plans for the future
